WEBVTT

00:01.392 --> 00:02.915
NARRATOR:
Previously onNinjago:

00:02.959 --> 00:05.744
MYSTAKEÉ:
You have good friends.
Lead them.

00:05.788 --> 00:07.398
And endure.

00:07.442 --> 00:10.662
IRON BARON:
Reveal the Oni!

00:10.706 --> 00:11.881
[♪♪♪]

00:11.924 --> 00:14.492
IRON BARON:
Hunt them down.

00:16.625 --> 00:18.453
[♪♪♪]

00:38.168 --> 00:39.735
[LAUGHS EVILLY]

00:41.258 --> 00:45.610
[NARRATOR READS ON-SCREEN TEXT]

00:45.654 --> 00:48.309
[CROWD CHANTING
INDISTINCTLY]

00:51.355 --> 00:54.924
They are Masters of Elements!

00:54.967 --> 00:57.666
A week's rations
for the hunter

00:57.709 --> 01:01.931
who brings them to me
in chains!

01:01.974 --> 01:02.975
I count 10.

01:03.019 --> 01:04.281
There are 15.

01:04.325 --> 01:06.457
Yeah, well, you were
always better with math.

01:06.501 --> 01:08.590
You with us, Jay?We're totally outnumbered.

01:08.633 --> 01:10.200
They have weapons
and we don't.

01:10.244 --> 01:11.419
I haven't eaten all day,

01:11.462 --> 01:12.985
not to mention
showered in a week.

01:13.029 --> 01:15.249
Do you see there are kids
in this audience?

01:15.292 --> 01:17.164
This level of violence
is far too much

01:17.207 --> 01:18.991
for them to handle,
let alone me!

01:19.035 --> 01:20.210
He's back to normal.

01:20.254 --> 01:22.256
Good.
Now that our secret's out,

01:22.299 --> 01:24.606
let's lay down some heat!

01:24.649 --> 01:25.868
[GRUNTS]

01:26.956 --> 01:28.871
[ALL GRUNTING]

01:34.050 --> 01:35.225
[WAILS]

01:37.097 --> 01:38.881
Hi-ya!

01:40.622 --> 01:43.364
Is the crowd cheering for us
or rooting against us?

01:43.407 --> 01:44.843
Ha! Does it matter?

01:44.887 --> 01:46.193
Yes. Yes, it does!

01:46.236 --> 01:50.284
[CHANTING]
Heavy Metal! Heavy Metal!

01:55.637 --> 01:58.814
Uh, I think
the crowd likes him.

02:04.820 --> 02:06.604
[YELLS][GRUNTS]

02:10.130 --> 02:11.870
[GRUNTS]

02:15.352 --> 02:17.180
[GASPS][GROANS]

02:21.228 --> 02:22.794
[ALL GRUNTING]

02:24.231 --> 02:27.756
The sword.
It attracts our power.

02:37.896 --> 02:39.855
[CROWD CHEERING]

02:42.205 --> 02:44.729
[LAUGHS]

02:45.469 --> 02:47.950
[ULTRA VIOLET ULULATES]

02:47.993 --> 02:50.474
[LAUGHS]

02:50.518 --> 02:53.216
The Mailman
doesn't deliver,

02:53.260 --> 02:56.306
so find him,
and return to sender!

02:56.350 --> 02:59.918
Today's jackpot
could be yours...

02:59.962 --> 03:00.963
[LAUGHS]

03:01.006 --> 03:04.227
Every day,
pick off our friends.

03:04.271 --> 03:05.750
Pick, pick, pick.

03:05.794 --> 03:08.362
Ugh.
As long as it's not me.

03:09.841 --> 03:12.757
Looks bigger than your other
builds. What are you making?

03:12.801 --> 03:15.847
Since we're outnumbered, we're
upping the armor and firepower.

03:15.891 --> 03:17.675
Thanks to some feedback
from Skylor,

03:17.719 --> 03:19.547
I feel like
it's really taking shape.

03:19.590 --> 03:20.678
But it's so bulky.

03:20.722 --> 03:22.245
We'll be sitting ducks
in that.

03:22.289 --> 03:23.855
It's a work in progress.

03:23.899 --> 03:25.248
She'll be ready.

03:25.292 --> 03:27.250
Karlof?

03:27.294 --> 03:30.340
Do you think I can get
your help with Lloyd's training?

03:30.384 --> 03:33.691
Ooh, it would
be my pleasure.

03:33.735 --> 03:36.128
Go easy on me.
I'm powerless.

03:36.172 --> 03:41.264
Eh. Actually, it won't be you
who will be facing Karlof,

03:41.308 --> 03:43.135
but Darreth.

03:43.179 --> 03:46.443
[CHUCKLING]
Me? I mean...

03:46.487 --> 03:50.273
All right. Hey, heh.
About time.

03:50.317 --> 03:52.275
But he isn't
an Elemental Master.

03:52.319 --> 03:53.624
Neither are you.

03:53.668 --> 03:57.149
Power takes many forms
beyond what is physical.

03:57.193 --> 04:01.110
The power of persuasion.
The power of numbers.

04:01.153 --> 04:03.330
The power to lead.

04:03.373 --> 04:07.159
Don't forget
power of metal.

04:07.203 --> 04:08.552
[♪♪♪]

04:08.596 --> 04:11.555
Oh, boy. You're gonna be
a tough nut to crack.

04:12.861 --> 04:13.992
Don't look at me.

04:14.036 --> 04:15.472
Lead him, son.

04:15.516 --> 04:17.648
You can do this,
Darreth.

04:17.692 --> 04:21.478
With the power of brown,
you're about to go down.

04:21.522 --> 04:22.523
Brown bear.

04:22.566 --> 04:26.091
[GROWLS, PANTING]

04:26.135 --> 04:27.658
Spiky penguin.

04:27.702 --> 04:29.834
[IMITATES PENGUIN]

04:31.532 --> 04:34.535
[GRUNTING]

04:34.578 --> 04:36.450
Lucky punch.
Come on, shake it off.

04:36.493 --> 04:37.886
[PANTING]

04:37.929 --> 04:40.541
LLOYD:
He's bigger.
So use your speed.

04:40.584 --> 04:43.326
Speed.
Like a cheetah.

04:43.370 --> 04:44.719
Darreth,
be nimble.

04:44.762 --> 04:47.069
Darreth, be quick.
Darreth jumped over the--

04:47.112 --> 04:49.463
[ALL GROAN]

04:49.506 --> 04:51.029
Lead.

04:51.073 --> 04:52.466
[MOANS]

04:52.509 --> 04:54.511
Ninja never quit.
Get up.

04:54.555 --> 04:55.817
[PANTING]

04:55.860 --> 04:57.427
[WHIMPERS]

04:57.471 --> 04:58.559
[ROARS]

04:58.602 --> 04:59.821
[DARRETH SCREAMS]

04:59.864 --> 05:02.563
DARRETH:
Fish! Slippery like a fish!

05:02.606 --> 05:04.739
[SCREAMING CONTINUES]

05:06.306 --> 05:08.003
[PANTING]

05:08.046 --> 05:10.440
I-I'm sorry, Lloyd, I--

05:10.484 --> 05:13.574
Oh, I let you down.

05:13.617 --> 05:15.793
I can't fight
everyone's fights.

05:15.837 --> 05:18.927
I'm sorry,
I couldn't hear that?

05:18.970 --> 05:21.277
I said
I can't fight everyone's--

05:21.321 --> 05:23.018
[♪♪♪]

05:23.061 --> 05:24.672
How do I lead
the resistance?

05:24.715 --> 05:27.152
By finding your voice.

05:27.196 --> 05:32.593
The more you inspire, the more
others will inspire you.

05:32.636 --> 05:34.899
And you better
find your voice soon,

05:34.943 --> 05:38.294
because today, you will
be taking back the airwaves.

05:38.338 --> 05:39.600
Airwaves?

05:39.643 --> 05:43.255
The people of Ninjago
think you're gone.

05:43.299 --> 05:45.780
Show them you're not.

05:46.737 --> 05:47.782
You heard her.

05:47.825 --> 05:50.350
Let's get
a plan together.

05:50.393 --> 05:52.003
[♪♪♪]

05:52.047 --> 05:54.963
[HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING][CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

06:00.664 --> 06:04.320
So you aren't Oni after all,

06:04.364 --> 06:08.368
but have trained in the arts
of the First Spinjitzu Master.

06:08.411 --> 06:09.586
You've heard of him?

06:09.630 --> 06:11.501
I've heard his legend.

06:11.545 --> 06:13.677
The coward who ran away.

06:13.721 --> 06:17.333
To-- What was it called?
Ninjengo?

06:17.377 --> 06:19.161
Uh, it's called Ninjago.

06:19.204 --> 06:21.163
And do you know
how to get us back?

06:21.206 --> 06:23.208
No. But even if I did,

06:23.252 --> 06:26.342
I have no interest
in helping you

06:26.386 --> 06:31.303
when there is so much
you Ninja can do for me here.

06:31.347 --> 06:32.609
Where are you taking us?

06:32.653 --> 06:36.221
Don't you know
power attracts power?

06:36.265 --> 06:38.702
We're hunting Dragons!

06:38.746 --> 06:40.574
[LAUGHING]

06:48.756 --> 06:50.888
Hey! Wasn't that our ship?

06:52.673 --> 06:55.023
Gas up the Dieselnaut,
Muzzle.

06:55.066 --> 06:56.764
[MUMBLING
INDISTINCTLY]

06:56.807 --> 06:58.548
Quit your
jibber-jabbering.

06:58.592 --> 07:01.159
Stop looking at me
that way, Arkade!

07:01.203 --> 07:04.685
You can fly by yourself
in that getup, Jet-Jack!

07:04.728 --> 07:06.861
Chewtoy,
is that what you're wearing?

07:06.904 --> 07:10.125
Ah, he's always
in a mood before a hunt,

07:10.168 --> 07:13.563
worried today might be the day
he comes across Firstbourne.

07:13.607 --> 07:15.696
[CHUCKLES]

07:17.132 --> 07:19.308
What do you
think you're doing?

07:19.351 --> 07:21.310
Uh... We've been asked
to lend a hand.

07:21.353 --> 07:25.445
Didn't I hear youse two
are from the Dangerbuff clan?

07:25.488 --> 07:28.056
Yep.Well, then I refuse

07:28.099 --> 07:29.753
to hunt with
either of you,

07:29.797 --> 07:31.799
because no Dangerbuff I know

07:31.842 --> 07:33.583
can shoot a hole
in the ground.

07:33.627 --> 07:35.977
Then stay at home,
tinsel toes,

07:36.020 --> 07:37.674
'cause the boss says
they need

07:37.718 --> 07:42.113
all the hands
he can get. And legs.

07:42.157 --> 07:43.854
[GRUNTS]

07:47.902 --> 07:49.469
[HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING]

07:49.512 --> 07:53.734
To the hunt! To the hunt!

07:53.777 --> 07:55.910
[♪♪♪]

08:08.183 --> 08:10.141
[♪♪♪]

08:21.892 --> 08:24.025
Does anyone wanna
go over the plan again?

08:24.068 --> 08:26.941
I'm good, but I still think
we could use more help,

08:26.984 --> 08:28.769
seeing that
the Broadcast Station

08:28.812 --> 08:31.206
is in Borg's Tower,
right under Garmadon's feet.

08:31.249 --> 08:33.687
All the more reason
to keep our footprint small.

08:33.730 --> 08:35.732
Do you know what
you're going to say?

08:35.776 --> 08:37.386
Uh, yeah, sure.

08:37.429 --> 08:38.648
He doesn't have a clue.

08:38.692 --> 08:39.867
That's not our problem.

08:39.910 --> 08:41.782
We just have to
get him up there.

08:43.566 --> 08:44.828
It's clear.
Let's move.

08:44.872 --> 08:47.004
[♪♪♪]

08:58.494 --> 08:59.800
[YELPS]

09:00.627 --> 09:02.542
[YELLS]

09:02.585 --> 09:04.369
[GRUNTS]

09:04.413 --> 09:06.546
[YELLING CONTINUES]

09:11.638 --> 09:13.161
[SIGHS]

09:13.204 --> 09:15.816
You summoned me,
Emperor?

09:15.859 --> 09:18.819
The city is too quiet.

09:18.862 --> 09:21.822
I feel the presence
of my son.

09:21.865 --> 09:24.476
He would be foolish
to show his face.

09:24.520 --> 09:26.566
Do I look like a fool?

09:26.609 --> 09:29.699
I will handle security
of the tower myself.

09:29.743 --> 09:32.484
I will not fail you.

09:33.790 --> 09:35.270
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

09:39.317 --> 09:41.102
ULTRA VIOLET:
Clock is still ticking,

09:41.145 --> 09:43.887
and the Mailman
hasn't been delivered.

09:43.931 --> 09:46.673
That means it's bonus time.

09:46.716 --> 09:49.066
[LAUGHS]

09:49.110 --> 09:52.374
And then he said,
"It wasn't me."

09:52.417 --> 09:53.505
[ALL LAUGHING]

09:53.549 --> 09:55.638
Keep your eyes peeled.

09:55.682 --> 09:57.161
The Emperor
senses something.

09:57.205 --> 10:00.904
Senses? Is that like some
new power he suddenly got?

10:00.948 --> 10:02.166
What do I know?

10:02.210 --> 10:05.387
Just don't make me look bad.

10:12.176 --> 10:13.482
What are you thinking,
Neuro?

10:13.525 --> 10:17.094
I'm thinking
what they are thinking.

10:17.138 --> 10:20.010
[DISTORTED]
Does anyone
like karaoke?

10:20.054 --> 10:23.840
You know what would be
awesome right now? Karaoke.

10:23.884 --> 10:25.842
Yeah, great idea.

10:25.886 --> 10:27.931
We was just thinking
the same thing.

10:27.975 --> 10:30.804
BIKERS [IN UNISON]:
♪ We're off to sing
At Laughy's ♪

10:30.847 --> 10:32.849
♪ A-diddly-doo-doo

10:32.893 --> 10:35.025
[♪♪♪]

10:43.599 --> 10:45.079
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

11:05.969 --> 11:08.102
[TAPS]

11:08.145 --> 11:10.321
This should be
the 81st floor.

11:10.365 --> 11:12.367
Television studio
right above us.

11:12.410 --> 11:15.457
LLOYD:
Good, this way.

11:23.595 --> 11:25.510
[HEAVY BREATHING]

11:26.947 --> 11:28.122
[GASPS]

11:31.778 --> 11:33.431
Come on.
Come on.

11:38.959 --> 11:40.134
Come on.

11:40.177 --> 11:42.310
[♪♪♪]

11:44.486 --> 11:48.055
You can absorb powers,
but have you ever combined them?

11:48.098 --> 11:49.926
I don't know.
Never tried.

11:49.970 --> 11:52.146
Then try.

11:54.365 --> 11:55.410
[GRUNTS]

12:06.856 --> 12:09.772
Something's not right.

12:09.816 --> 12:12.383
I feel...

12:12.427 --> 12:15.778
My Emperor,
is everything okay?

12:15.822 --> 12:17.171
He's close.

12:17.214 --> 12:19.477
He must be on
the next floor. Hurry.

12:25.048 --> 12:26.571
[SIGHS]

12:26.615 --> 12:28.312
You learn something
every day.

12:28.356 --> 12:31.054
We're almost there.
Come on.

12:38.670 --> 12:41.021
Hope you're comfortable.

12:41.064 --> 12:43.284
Argh. Whatever you
have planned for us,

12:43.327 --> 12:45.068
we'll never help you
hunt Dragons.

12:45.112 --> 12:47.941
Hm. I beg to differ.

12:47.984 --> 12:49.681
[BUZZING]

12:49.725 --> 12:51.640
[ALL LAUGHING]

12:55.426 --> 12:57.951
He's triggering
an elemental reaction.

12:57.994 --> 13:00.780
[LAUGHS]

13:00.823 --> 13:03.173
Is that what he means by
power attracts power?

13:03.217 --> 13:05.175
[GASPS]
He's using us as bait.

13:05.219 --> 13:07.656
[GIGGLES]

13:07.699 --> 13:08.962
And it kinda tickles.

13:09.005 --> 13:13.053
I'm excited to see what
tonight's catch brings!

13:13.096 --> 13:16.230
[NINJA LAUGHING]

13:18.493 --> 13:21.322
How are we supposed to
rescue them way up there?

13:21.365 --> 13:23.063
In short, we don't.

13:23.106 --> 13:24.586
Not until they're alone.

13:24.629 --> 13:27.894
Hm... Why don't you
join us, Dangerbuff?

13:27.937 --> 13:29.852
[CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

13:31.158 --> 13:32.899
CHEWTOY:
Sit down and listen to me.

13:32.942 --> 13:35.292
They never do,
do they?

13:38.165 --> 13:40.776
Uh, that's some blade
you have there.

13:40.820 --> 13:42.996
Crazy how it repelled
those powers.

13:43.039 --> 13:45.650
Oh, yeah.
Carved from Dragonbone.

13:45.694 --> 13:47.783
From a piece
of the Firstbourne.

13:47.827 --> 13:48.828
Firstbourne?

13:48.871 --> 13:50.917
Hey, where you been,
Dangerbuff?

13:50.960 --> 13:53.136
In the belly of Beetlenut?

13:53.180 --> 13:55.356
[ALL LAUGH]

13:56.618 --> 13:59.795
Firstbourne is
the mother of all Dragons.

13:59.839 --> 14:01.579
The most powerful
in the Realm.

14:01.623 --> 14:03.973
No one's ever seen it entirely,

14:04.017 --> 14:08.456
but it is said to possess every
element of her beloved spawn.

14:08.499 --> 14:12.677
The one prize that's
always eluded Iron Baron.

14:12.721 --> 14:13.853
[SPITS]

14:13.896 --> 14:15.202
Tell 'em, Jet-Jack.

14:15.245 --> 14:17.944
She took Baron's leg.

14:17.987 --> 14:20.990
Then his arm.

14:21.034 --> 14:22.905
Then his pride.

14:22.949 --> 14:25.255
But someone here
got a piece of her,

14:25.299 --> 14:27.431
didn't you, Heavy Metal?

14:29.651 --> 14:33.481
Iron Baron's been searching
for her nest all his life.

14:33.524 --> 14:37.311
Said she protects there
the Dragon Armor.

14:37.354 --> 14:38.573
Dragon Armor?

14:38.616 --> 14:40.836
Worn by
the First Spinjitzu Master.

14:40.880 --> 14:43.883
Whoever controls the armor,
controls Firstbourne.

14:43.926 --> 14:48.757
And he who controls Firstbourne,
can protect us from the Oni.

14:48.800 --> 14:49.889
Oni?

14:49.932 --> 14:51.891
[ALL CHEER]

14:51.934 --> 14:54.545
[SPITTING]

14:54.589 --> 14:59.637
When the Oni see me riding
on the mother of all Dragons.

14:59.681 --> 15:01.378
MAN 1:
That will be the day.

15:01.422 --> 15:02.902
MAN 2:
It's gonna be me, you know.

15:02.945 --> 15:05.469
The Oni?
What do they look like?

15:05.513 --> 15:07.907
He's right--[WIND BLOWS]

15:07.950 --> 15:08.995
Dragon!

15:09.038 --> 15:10.735
[ALL YELLING]

15:10.779 --> 15:12.955
Don't just stand there,
Dangerbuff!

15:12.999 --> 15:14.348
Man the turret!

15:14.391 --> 15:17.133
[NINJA LAUGHING]Where is she?

15:17.177 --> 15:19.396
[DRAGON GROWLS]

15:19.440 --> 15:20.397
There! There!

15:20.441 --> 15:22.573
[♪♪♪]

15:24.662 --> 15:27.448
Guys. I really
don't like this.

15:27.491 --> 15:29.058
A Wind Dragon.

15:29.102 --> 15:30.930
And a good-sized one too.

15:30.973 --> 15:32.453
Lay low! Let her come.

15:35.543 --> 15:39.068
Wait for it... Wait for it.

15:48.338 --> 15:49.513
Now!

15:51.341 --> 15:52.734
Take the shot,
Dangerbuff!

15:52.777 --> 15:54.388
What are you waiting for?

16:01.351 --> 16:02.787
[NINJA SCREAM]

16:03.614 --> 16:05.051
Oh, no. My mistake.

16:05.094 --> 16:08.315
I should've known
to never trust a Dangerbuff.

16:08.358 --> 16:09.838
Get out of there!

16:09.881 --> 16:11.883
Now's our chance.
Let's get them.

16:16.801 --> 16:21.110
She's making a run for it!
Follow her!

16:21.154 --> 16:23.025
[HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING]

16:23.895 --> 16:24.809
What?

16:27.464 --> 16:30.119
You heard the Baron.
Get a move on!

16:44.612 --> 16:47.963
Ha, ha. She's fast as the wind,
I'll give her that!

17:07.200 --> 17:08.592
[ROARS]

17:09.419 --> 17:11.160
[ROARING CONTINUES]

17:23.303 --> 17:25.479
We're losing her!

17:48.023 --> 17:50.156
[HUNTERS CHEERING
AND CHATTERING]

17:54.377 --> 17:56.031
[DRAGON GROANS]

17:56.075 --> 17:58.816
So tonight
wasn't our night.

17:58.860 --> 18:00.427
It wasn't hers,
either.

18:00.470 --> 18:02.298
We'll figure out
a way out of this.

18:02.342 --> 18:05.084
For us,
and the Dragons.

18:07.216 --> 18:09.088
[GAME SHOW MUSIC PLAYING]

18:09.131 --> 18:11.699
So what?
You help us catch everyone else,

18:11.742 --> 18:14.310
but no one knows
where the Mailman is?

18:14.354 --> 18:15.659
He's just a postal worker,

18:15.703 --> 18:18.009
why have we not
caught him, people?

18:18.053 --> 18:19.489
[DOOR OPENS][MUSIC STOPS]

18:19.533 --> 18:21.709
[FOOTSTEPS THUDDING][PUNCHES LANDING]

18:23.624 --> 18:25.756
[STATIC CRACKLING]

18:29.891 --> 18:31.197
[GRUNTS]

18:32.111 --> 18:33.851
Hi-ya![YELLS]

18:36.202 --> 18:37.899
This is a closed set!

18:37.942 --> 18:39.161
Sorry, UV.

18:39.205 --> 18:41.642
But your show
has just been canceled.

18:43.296 --> 18:44.340
[SCREAMS]

18:44.384 --> 18:45.428
Uh, uh, uh.

18:45.472 --> 18:47.126
[GROANS]

18:47.169 --> 18:49.084
[GRUNTING]

18:52.218 --> 18:53.306
All right, Lloyd.

18:56.744 --> 18:58.963
Once we go live,
it'll only be a matter of time

18:59.007 --> 19:02.141
before they know we're here.
Are you ready?

19:02.184 --> 19:07.842
Then we're live in
five, four, three, two...

19:08.538 --> 19:10.105
[BEEPS]

19:10.149 --> 19:11.193
[GASPS]

19:11.237 --> 19:13.587
Hello, Ninjago.
It's me.

19:13.630 --> 19:16.024
Lloyd Garmadon.
The Green Ninja...

19:16.067 --> 19:20.028
You said he was gone.
Look, the Green Ninja.

19:20.071 --> 19:23.684
The Green Ninja's alive?

19:23.727 --> 19:27.209
Anyone?
Anyone?

19:27.253 --> 19:30.038
This is why
I'm going out of business...

19:30.081 --> 19:32.519
Lord Garmadon
wants you to be afraid,

19:32.562 --> 19:34.129
but I need you to be brave.

19:34.173 --> 19:37.785
With the help of
Princess Harumi,

19:37.828 --> 19:39.787
Lord Garmadon
struck a major blow

19:39.830 --> 19:41.441
against Ninjago City--

19:41.484 --> 19:44.226
[SCREAMS]

19:44.270 --> 19:46.663
♪ Yeah

19:46.707 --> 19:49.362
--We're ready to strike back.

19:49.405 --> 19:50.450
[GROANS]

19:50.493 --> 19:52.365
There is a resistance.

19:52.408 --> 19:54.280
And we may be small--

19:54.323 --> 19:56.282
[PANTING][KEYBOARD CLACKING]

19:56.325 --> 19:59.067
but we are power--

20:02.853 --> 20:05.334
--p-powerful.

20:13.081 --> 20:16.127
Come on, Lloyd,
get it together.

20:17.868 --> 20:18.826
[GASPS]

20:18.869 --> 20:21.698
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

20:21.742 --> 20:22.960
[BANGS]

20:24.527 --> 20:25.659
[GRUNTS]

20:25.702 --> 20:27.661
Hurry. Hurry!

20:27.704 --> 20:29.402
[GRUNTING]

20:35.277 --> 20:38.280
I may not have
elemental power,

20:38.324 --> 20:41.022
but I call upon
the power of the people.

20:41.065 --> 20:44.417
When we get knocked down,
we rise up.

20:44.460 --> 20:46.027
Stronger than before.

20:46.070 --> 20:48.638
This is our city.

20:48.682 --> 20:51.075
He thinks he can bully us
with stone giants.

20:51.119 --> 20:53.904
Well this isn't the first time our city has faced ruin.

20:53.948 --> 20:55.906
Buildings fall,

20:55.950 --> 20:57.952
but we rise!

20:57.995 --> 21:00.911
[CROWD CHEERS]

21:00.955 --> 21:04.393
And to you, Father,
I say this:

21:04.437 --> 21:07.396
Fighting me may
make you feel powerful,

21:07.440 --> 21:11.139
but you're about to see
what real power is.

21:11.182 --> 21:13.837
The resistance never quits.

21:13.881 --> 21:18.494
He has found his voice.

21:18.538 --> 21:20.453
[ROARS]

21:22.237 --> 21:24.544
LLOYD [ON TV]:
The resistance never quits.

21:24.587 --> 21:29.766
[LOOPING]
